page.title: 03Local news, Stickney.
page.content: An exibition was held at the new village hall in Stickney in April 1985.A man organised the exibition about the history of Stickney.He had drawn and written everything.It was very interesting there. Most of the local news is concerning the church.Some of it is about the annual parochial church council meetings where a group of people go and discuss future events. Last week there was news of the T.Y.E.group.This is a group of young people who talk and do things for the church and raise money for appeals. They try to help in the best way possible.Some of the local parishioners have joined the Rev J.R Worsdal to help dig a trench to enable the water to be laid on to the church.
